# Using Build Meta-data

In this guide we’ll walk through using the Buildkite Agent’s [meta-data command](/docs/agent/cli-meta-data) to store and retrieve data between different steps in a build pipeline.

<%= toc %>

## Setting data

To set meta-data, use the `set` command with a key/value pair:

```bash
buildkite-agent meta-data set "release-version" "1.1"
```

## Getting data

To retrieve meta-data in a later step, use the `get` command with the previously set key:

```bash
buildkite-agent meta-data get "release-version"
```

## Further documentation

See the [Buildkite Agent build meta-data documentation](/docs/agent/cli-meta-data) for a full list of options and details of Buildkite’s meta-data support.